    "body": "**Describe the bug**\r\nI set the `spark.rapids.memory.host.spillStorageSize` to one byte and the logs for the task show it is spilling to disk and yet the stage level spill metrics show it as a host side spill at the top of the image on the left.\r\n\r\n![image](https://github.com/NVIDIA/spark-rapids/assets/20541681/f7e14ec7-761b-48eb-b4ae-0b3d333978b3)\r\n\r\n\r\n**Steps/Code to reproduce bug**\r\nset the `spark.rapids.memory.host.spillStorageSize` to one byte, Run something like \r\n\r\n```\r\nimport spark.implicits._\r\nimport org.apache.spark.sql.functions._\r\n\r\nspark.conf.set(\"spark.databricks.optimizer.adaptive.enabled\", \"false\")\r\nspark.conf.set(\"spark.sql.shuffle.partitions\", 1)\r\nspark.conf.set(\"spark.sql.adaptive.coalescePartitions.enabled\", \"false\")\r\nval df1 = spark.range(1000000000)\r\nval df2 = spark.range(1000000000)\r\n\r\nval df3 = df1.unionAll(df2)\r\nval df4 = df3.sort(col(\"id\"))\r\ndf4.groupBy(\"id\").count.show\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\nShow that same number as disk spilled bytes\r\n**Environment details (please complete the following information)**\r\n - Databricks Azure although this is platform independent bug\r\n\r\nSpark config for the cluster on DB Azure\r\n```\r\nspark.rapids.shuffle.enabled true\r\nspark.shuffle.manager com.nvidia.spark.rapids.spark330db.RapidsShuffleManager\r\nspark.executor.cores 1\r\nspark.eventLog.enabled true\r\nspark.rapids.memory.host.spillStorageSize 1\r\nspark.plugins com.nvidia.spark.SQLPlugin\r\nspark.rapids.sql.explain ALL\r\nspark.rapids.shuffle.compression.codec lz4\r\nspark.eventLog.dir dbfs:/cluster-logs/\r\nspark.rapids.sql.enabled true\r\n```\r\n\r\n",
